snippet: After five decades of military rule and a series of rigged or canceled elections, voters took part in what many described as their first genuine election.
abstract: Voters in Myanmar are thrilled to participate in what many describe as first real elections they have witnessed in their lifetimes; preliminary results suggests opposition National League for Democracy, led by Daw Aung San Suu Kyi, is leading in polls, although it may take days for final results to be tallied; remains unclear how country's military leadership will accept results.
lead_paragraph: After five decades of military rule and a series of rigged or canceled elections, voters took part in what many described as their first genuine election.

headline.main: Myanmar’s People Joyful in Voting, Even With Final Results Days Away
headline.print_headline: In Pause Before Results, Myanmar Exults in Vote
